1
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,733
<i>- Stay right there!
- Hey! Jeff!</i>

2
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,100
<i>What did you do? And who's that?</i>

3
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> Dad, he's Hazel's accomplice.</i>

4
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:19,967
<i>He's one of the guys
who kidnapped me.</i>

5
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,800
<i>He also helped Hazel escape
from jail.</i>

6
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,600
<i> You bastard!</i>

7
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:25,067
<i> You're both monsters!</i>

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>Where's the helicopter?
Where's my 20 million pesos?</i>

9
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,133
<i> We're working on it, Hazel.</i>

10
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>We already have six million.
We're still raising the rest.</i>

11
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:33,500
<i> Hazel, don't believe Ferrer!</i>

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,200
<i> I know her. She's a liar!</i>

13
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>There's no helicopter!
No 20 million!</i>

14
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,100
<i> You played me!</i>

15
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:41,100
<i>This is payback
for what you did!</i>

16
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:46,533
<i> Don't hurt Felma!</i>

17
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,967
<i> Stop it, please. Have mercy!</i>

18
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:54,167
<i>Eagle eye, do we
have a clear shot?</i>

19
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:56,600
<i>Target and hostage
are too close.</i>

20
00:00:58,767 --> 00:00:59,600
<i> That's it!</i>

21
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:00,833
<i>That's it!
Come on, Mom! Fight back!</i>

22
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:02,767
<i> I'm not dying!</i>

23
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:04,100
<i> Not today, Hazel!</i>

24
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:06,267
<i> And not because of you!</i>

25
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:10,100
<i> Hazel Capistrano!</i>

26
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:15,367
<i>This is Mayor Hermie Constancio,
at your service.</i>

27
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:18,500
<i>Ma'am, with all due respect,
this is a police operation.</i>

28
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:22,400
<i>Don't forget
you're on my turf.</i>

29
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:24,800
<i> Enough! My wife's in danger.</i>

30
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:26,133
<i>That's what we need to focus on.</i>

31
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:28,200
<i> We all have the same goal.</i>

32
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:31,433
<i>To end this peacefully. So
please, let's work together.</i>

33
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:32,500
<i> Hazel!</i>

34
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,333
<i> Same demands, Mayor.</i>

35
00:01:34,467 --> 00:01:37,033
<i>Helicopter and
20 million pesos.</i>

36
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,933
<i>I want everything
here in 30 minutes!</i>

37
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:41,800
<i> No problem, Hazel.</i>

38
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,233
<i> I'm just asking one thing.</i>

39
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:46,133
<i> Let Felma go.</i>

40
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:55,833
I'm not releasing
Felma yet.

41
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:59,767
I need to get where
I'm going first.

42
00:02:00,933 --> 00:02:02,567
Do you think I'm crazy?

43
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,533
I know what
you're planning.

44
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,067
You can't trick me.

45
00:02:07,633 --> 00:02:08,900
You know, I like you.

46
00:02:09,033 --> 00:02:11,300
You're easy to deal with.

47
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:14,233
That's good. That's what I want.

48
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,367
Well...

49
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,833
my brother,

50
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,567
back in college,

51
00:02:22,167 --> 00:02:25,800
took his girlfriend hostage,
too.

52
00:02:25,933 --> 00:02:28,600
Then he suddenly
changed his mind.

53
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:35,000
When the cops showed up,
he just wanted to disappear.

54
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:39,500
He didn't know what to do.
He just wanted it all to end.

55
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:42,167
But he never got the chance.

56
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,100
He was killed.

57
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:50,200
So, now...

58
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:54,100
I'm giving you the chance
my brother never had.

59
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:57,167
A way out.

60
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,000
A clean break.

61
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:02,600
I promise,

62
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:05,633
no one will know where you go.

63
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:09,733
But I'm asking one thing.

64
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:15,000
Don't drag Felma into this.
Let her go.

65
00:03:15,133 --> 00:03:16,900
I'll go with you
to the helicopter.

66
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:20,200
I'll take you
wherever you want.

67
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:22,100
Ma'am, that's dangerous.

68
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:28,833
I'm willing to
sacrifice myself.

69
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,733
Once the hostage is safe,

70
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:43,267
the mayor will probably call
a press conference.

71
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:47,433
Obviously, she's just doing it
for a show.

72
00:03:47,567 --> 00:03:49,400
She's running for Congress.

73
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,667
I've got some info, Ma'am.

74
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,733
I know someone on the resort
staff. I already called him.

75
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:59,100
Yes, we can go live at any time.

76
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,933
Guys, let's move.

77
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:04,433
So, Hazel,

78
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:08,333
have you made a decision?

79
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:22,033
Hazel, come on.
Listen to the Mayor.

80
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:24,800
- Let Felma go.
- Yes.

81
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,267
Manuel?

82
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:29,633
Manuel, please, be patient.

83
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,400
That's Manuel, right?

84
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,167
I want to talk to Manuel.

85
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:34,667
I'll talk to him.

86
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,233
Wait.

87
00:04:37,367 --> 00:04:40,867
Hazel, I'm the one talking
to you.

88
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:46,067
Mayor, I've made my decision,
but I want to talk to Manuel.

89
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,900
I want Manuel.

90
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:52,933
Hazel.

91
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:56,667
Manuel.

92
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:07,567
Hazel Capistrano is one
of the inmates who escaped

93
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:10,767
from the city jail two days ago.

94
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:11,933
There's still
no official statement

95
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:14,000
from Solara Marcela Hotel
and Resort,

96
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:18,700
but Mayor Constancio is on site,
assisting with negotiations.

97
00:05:20,133 --> 00:05:21,700
What is this?

98
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:23,467
Why am I on the news?

99
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,233
Back in February 2023,

100
00:05:25,367 --> 00:05:28,967
Mayor Constancio rescued Isidro
Nava after he was taken hostage

101
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:31,733
by Virgilio Lumaque
in San Matias.

102
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:33,400
Two months later,

103
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:37,967
the suspect was tracked down
after an anonymous tip.

104
00:05:38,133 --> 00:05:40,367
Are you going to do that to me,
too?

105
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,033
Are you going to sell me out?

106
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:43,333
What?

107
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:45,933
What are you talking about?

108
00:05:46,067 --> 00:05:48,967
You're going to paint me like
that Virgilio Lumaque guy?

109
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,433
I don't know!

110
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,100
I don't know anything
about that!

111
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:59,067
Believe me, Hazel.
I'm telling the truth.

112
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:02,433
You animals! You're all animals!

113
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:05,700
You're ganging up on me!
You're liars!

114
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:09,400
All of you are traitors!
Everyone of you! Traitors!

115
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:16,233
They're going to kill me!

116
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,633
They'll kill me!

117
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:22,300
They said they'd help me!

118
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:25,033
They said they'd help me!

119
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:26,067
Hazel...

120
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,767
- All I ever wanted...
- Hazel.

121
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:30,967
- I just wanted to be loved.
- Hazel!

122
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,667
I just wanted to be loved.
Why is it so hard?

123
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,300
Why can't they give me that?

124
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:39,667
Why does everyone
always leave me?

125
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,967
Jojo. Jessica.

126
00:06:42,133 --> 00:06:44,700
Even Manuel. They left me.

127
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:46,000
They all left me.

128
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:48,600
I'm so tired.

129
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,467
I'm so tired!

130
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:55,133
Hazel, turn yourself in.

131
00:06:55,267 --> 00:06:57,067
Please, surrender.

132
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,567
No. No, I won't.

133
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,133
They're going to kill me.

134
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:05,433
No, Felma, no!

135
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:08,233
I don't want to die, Felma!

136
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,600
Hazel...

137
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:16,167
- They're going to kill me!
- Turn yourself in.

138
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:23,667
- Hazel!
- Dad!

139
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,467
Hazel! That's enough!

140
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,300
Let Felma go!

141
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:30,367
My wife needs me!

142
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,867
My wife needs me!

143
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,433
Take me instead!

144
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:36,633
- Dad, stop it.
- Stop it, Dad.

145
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:39,667
Leave Felma alone!
Take me instead!

146
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,367
Me!

147
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,767
Hazel, stop this!

148
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,867
Hello?

149
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,300
I heard Manuel.

150
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:02,767
I want to talk to him.

151
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,833
Send him up here. I need him.

152
00:08:10,633 --> 00:08:13,800
Eagle Eye,
do you have eyes inside?

153
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:15,633
Command, negative.
No visual on the suspect.

154
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,567
What's taking Manuel so long?

155
00:08:32,633 --> 00:08:36,333
- What's taking Manuel so long?
- Hazel...

156
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:39,767
Whatever you're planning,
please...

157
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:46,000
Don't make a sound.
I'm waiting for Manuel.

158
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:47,767
Be quiet.

159
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,633
Be quiet, Felma.

160
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:53,900
Just leave me here.

161
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,333
Take care, Sir.

162
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,300
Don't make a sound.

163
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,367
Manuel, where are you?

164
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:15,067
Hazel.

165
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:33,200
Hazel.

166
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:37,067
Hazel, I'm the one you want,
right?

167
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:40,267
Hurt me instead. Let Felma go!

168
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,567
Hazel!

169
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:43,733
Hazel.

170
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:50,133
Hazel!

171
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:51,967
Hazel, I'm here!

172
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,367
Hazel.

173
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:57,633
Please, Hazel. I'm begging you.

174
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:01,133
Let's end this.

175
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:03,533
Hazel, let Felma go.

176
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:14,500
How did Hazel find out
about the Nava-Lumaque case?

177
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:21,100
It was reported by Amiel
Navarro, PNTV 42 News Live.

178
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:28,100
Get that reporter in
my office first thing tomorrow!

179
00:10:32,467 --> 00:10:36,333
My God, why did they give
in to Hazel's demands?

180
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,567
Why did they let
Manuel go up there?

181
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:42,300
Because Hazel would've
killed Mom if Dad hadn't gone.

182
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,333
That's what Manuel wanted.

183
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:46,800
Better him than Felma.

184
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:51,200
But what if Hazel kills
both Mom and Dad?

185
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,033
Do you think Manuel
would let that happen?

186
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,533
With how angry Manuel is...

187
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:02,933
he might even kill Hazel.

188
00:11:03,067 --> 00:11:04,867
Eagle Eye.

189
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,200
Command.

190
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:08,400
Situation's escalating.

191
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:11,200
You are clear to engage
at your discretion.

192
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:13,467
Copy. Standing by.

193
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:19,300
Hazel.

194
00:11:21,467 --> 00:11:23,200
Hazel.

195
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:25,400
I'm begging you.

196
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:27,300
Don't hurt Manuel.

197
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:34,767
I won't hurt the person
I love most, Felma.

198
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:40,100
I asked Manuel to
come here because...

199
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,567
because I need help.

200
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:46,467
What kind of help?

201
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:50,800
Get up.

202
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:53,933
Get up.

203
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:13,000
Open the door.

204
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:14,700
Open it!

205
00:12:36,967 --> 00:12:38,167
Manuel.

206
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:56,200
Hazel, stop.

207
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:57,667
I'm here.

208
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,367
End this now.

209
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,967
Hazel!

210
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,033
Stop.

211
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,467
Please don't let it go this far.

212
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,900
Enough, Hazel.

213
00:13:40,033 --> 00:13:41,033
That's enough, okay?

214
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,467
Enough, please.

215
00:13:59,267 --> 00:14:00,900
It's too late now, Manuel.

216
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,700
This already happened.

217
00:14:07,633 --> 00:14:09,733
All of this happened because...

218
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,367
you didn't love me.

219
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:18,867
Hazel, you know why.

220
00:14:22,567 --> 00:14:25,200
Even before I met you,

221
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,233
my heart already belonged
to someone else.

222
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,200
You knew that.

223
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:36,633
But I tried. Didn't I?
I even married you.

224
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,767
I believed it was the right
thing to do.

225
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:45,467
Even if it meant being separated
from my family.

226
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:51,800
Hazel, listen to me.

227
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,400
I tried to love you.

228
00:14:57,867 --> 00:14:59,500
I really did.

229
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:03,500
But I just couldn't.

230
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:08,567
My heart only beats
for one person.

231
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:11,167
But...

232
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:17,533
you became an important
part of my life.

233
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:20,167
When I lost my children,

234
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:24,900
you gave me a chance
to be a father again.

235
00:15:25,033 --> 00:15:26,900
Because of Jessica.

236
00:15:30,933 --> 00:15:33,933
Even if she wasn't really...

237
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:35,600
Even if she wasn't really
your child?

238
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:39,333
Still, I'm grateful.
It's true, Hazel.

239
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:42,800
You know why?

240
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:45,033
Because she became
part of my life.

241
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:50,733
And that can never be
erased from my memory.

242
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:57,100
You know in my heart,
there'll always be that moment,

243
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:00,700
that time when, in some way,

244
00:16:02,367 --> 00:16:03,967
we were a family.

245
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:09,300
But that's all it
can ever be, Hazel.

246
00:16:09,467 --> 00:16:11,133
Just a memory.

247
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,433
Hazel...

248
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:22,300
You've wronged me deeply.

249
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:23,767
Deeply.

250
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:30,367
But I admit,
I also wronged you.

251
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:32,200
Because...

252
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:35,233
I couldn't return
the love you gave me.

253
00:16:39,367 --> 00:16:40,933
Hazel...

254
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,200
forgive me.

255
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:44,833
The truth is...

256
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:48,567
I did love you.

257
00:16:51,867 --> 00:16:54,367
Just not in the
way you wanted.

258
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:59,467
Not in the way you needed.

259
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:10,100
Help me, Manuel.

260
00:17:11,133 --> 00:17:14,000
Manuel, I'm scared.

261
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,467
- They're going to kill me.
- No, Hazel.

262
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:16,967
- They're going to kill me.
- No.

263
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,567
We'll help you.

264
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,467
We'll help you
get out of this.

265
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:24,633
I don't want to get out.

266
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,667
- They're going to kill me.
- No!

267
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,133
No! I don't want to die!
They're going to kill me!

268
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:31,067
Hazel, don't be afraid.
We'll help you!

269
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,900
- No! I don't want to!
- Hazel!

270
00:17:33,033 --> 00:17:35,900
I don't want to go out there!
They're going to kill me!

271
00:17:36,033 --> 00:17:38,933
- They said they'd kill me!
- Hazel, we'll help you.

272
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:41,133
- Hazel, listen to me.
- I don't want to.

273
00:17:41,267 --> 00:17:43,933
- No, Hazel.
- No! I don't want to go out.

274
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:46,433
- Hazel, listen. We'll help you.
- I don't want to!

275
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:52,800
What's happening in there?

276
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:58,967
What if Hazel already
killed Dad,

277
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:00,700
and she's going to kill Mom
next?

278
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:04,400
Oh God, please, no.

279
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:08,533
All units, move in carefully.

280
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,333
Eagle Eye, status?

281
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:16,833
Command, no eye on the suspect.

282
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,267
I don't want to!

283
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:24,800
I don't want to!
You're going to turn me in!

284
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:27,300
- I don't want to!
- Hazel!

285
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:29,167
- Wait, Hazel, listen!
- No!

286
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,200
They're going to kill me!

287
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:33,300
Hazel, no one's going to kill
you. We'll help you!

288
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:34,200
- I don't want to!
- Hazel!

289
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:37,267
Command, target acquired.

290
00:18:44,867 --> 00:18:46,100
- Step away from the window!
- They're going to kill me!

291
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:49,367
Step away from the window,
Hazel! Listen to me!

292
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:51,400
Mom!

293
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:53,300
Ma'am!

294
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:55,767
Hazel, step away
from the window!

295
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,700
No one's going to kill you!

296
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:03,600
- I don't want to!
- Step away from the window!

297
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:09,233
- Come on, let's help Mom.
- Stop! Nobody move!

298
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:17,033
- Hazel!
- Hazel!

299
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:19,067
Hazel!

300
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,267
Command, suspect down.

301
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:25,800
Felma!

302
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:34,933
- Hazel!
- Hazel!

303
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,300
Hazel!

304
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:38,167
Put pressure on the wound.

305
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,167
Stop the bleeding!

306
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,967
- Help!
- Help!

307
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,300
Help!

308
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,633
Help!

309
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,467
Hazel...

310
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,867
We don't want you to die, Hazel.

311
00:19:57,667 --> 00:20:01,033
Help me. I don't want to die.

312
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,567
Yes, we'll help you.

313
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,633
We'll help you, Hazel.

314
00:20:04,767 --> 00:20:06,133
Let's wait for help.

315
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:11,000
Manuel, Manuel, go get
help from outside.

316
00:20:11,133 --> 00:20:13,133
Manuel, forgive me.

317
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:14,433
Hazel...

318
00:20:14,567 --> 00:20:22,033
Thank you. Thank you
for loving me and Jessica.

319
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,567
Yes, Hazel.

320
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:25,433
I forgive you.

321
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:27,467
I forgive you.

322
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,133
Hazel, Hazel,
don't talk anymore.

323
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:31,733
- Come on.
- Manuel.

324
00:20:31,867 --> 00:20:33,500
Help!

325
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,300
- Help!
- Hazel...

326
00:20:36,467 --> 00:20:40,900
Hazel, Hazel, Hazel, hang on.

327
00:20:41,033 --> 00:20:42,400
Don't give up.

328
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:44,100
You're going to live.

329
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:46,000
There's still time.

330
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:49,100
There's still hope.
You can still change.

331
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,367
Felma...

332
00:20:54,233 --> 00:20:57,700
Forgive me.

333
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:01,567
I've hurt you so much.

334
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:03,500
Forgive me.

335
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,733
I forgive you.

336
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,533
Hazel...

337
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:09,933
Hazel?

338
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:12,300
Hazel!

339
00:21:12,433 --> 00:21:15,367
Hazel! Fight, Hazel!

340
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,633
Hazel!

341
00:21:20,367 --> 00:21:22,067
Hazel!

342
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:24,100
Hazel!

343
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:25,600
Manuel!

344
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,533
Help!

345
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,133
Hazel!

346
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:36,033
I forgive you.

347
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,400
I forgive you.

348
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,467
Mom.

349
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:46,267
Mom!

350
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:49,500
- Ma'am!
- Mom!

351
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:50,967
Felma!

352
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,267
Manuel!

353
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,967
- Oh my god!
- Easy, easy.

354
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:54,900
Mom.

355
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:56,467
Mom, you're hurt.

356
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:57,700
Felma.

357
00:21:57,833 --> 00:22:00,167
Thank God you're safe!

358
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:01,800
Oh god, Mom.

359
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,200
- Mom.
- Pretty Grandmother.

360
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:19,900
Handsome Grandfather.

361
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,133
Wait.

362
00:22:24,267 --> 00:22:25,233
Just a second.

363
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:26,600
- Just a second, please.
- Wait for a second.

364
00:23:09,667 --> 00:23:11,333
I love you, my love.

365
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,800
I love you too, my love.

366
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:01,000
- Smells like jealousy.
- Jessica...

367
00:24:01,133 --> 00:24:02,733
Jessica, I mean Didang.

368
00:24:02,867 --> 00:24:04,733
It's a good thing my eyelashes
didn't get stuck.

369
00:24:06,567 --> 00:24:07,333
Cut!

370
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:10,100
Rolling.

371
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:16,500
She couldn't accept that...

372
00:24:16,633 --> 00:24:18,200
Sorry.

373
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:20,467
- I choked.
- He choked.

374
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,600
- You idiot!
- Cut!

375
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:23,767
I got deaf.

376
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,700
That was so loud.

377
00:24:25,833 --> 00:24:28,433
Didn't you know it's guilty...

378
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:30,267
until proven guilty?

379
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,733
I mean, innocent.

380
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:34,900
Innocent until proven guilty.

381
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:38,400
I broke it! Sorry!

382
00:24:38,533 --> 00:24:39,767
This song
makes me want to dance.
